{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Chocolate Sponge","content":["Preheat oven to 180°C and line base of a spring form tin (Ø 26 cm) with baking paper."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place eggs and sugar in mixing bowl then mix <b>1 min\/speed 4<b>.","Add flour, cocoa powder and baking powder then mix <b>20 sec\/speed 2.5<b>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong> then finish mixing by hand with spatula. Transfer to prepared tin, smooth down to form an even layer then bake for 10 minutes (180°C). Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl and butterfly whisk.","Allow sponge to cool for 5 minutes in tin before removing to a wire rack to cool completely.","Once cool, cut into 2 cm cubes then divide between 8 individual serving bowls or one large serving dish. Press sponge down slightly."]},{"title":"Topping","content":["Drain peach halves through simmering basket collecting juice in a bowl below. Cut peaches in 1 cm pieces.","Drizzle 1 ½ tsp reserved peach juice over sponge in each serving bowl then arrange peach pieces evenly over sponge layer."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place cream in mixing bowl and whip <b>without setting a time\/speed 3<b> watching carefully to avoid over-whipping.","Add mascarpone and vanilla sugar then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then mix again <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>. Spread evenly over peach pieces in serving bowls then set aside in fridge to chill for at least 30 minutes. Meanwhile, toast flaked almonds in a non-stick frying pan until browned, then set aside to cool.","Sprinkle cooled, toasted almonds over chilled trifles before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Chocolate Sponge","content":["3 large eggs","100 g caster sugar","90 g plain flour","20 g cocoa powder","½ tsp baking powder"]},{"title":"Topping","content":["2 tins peach halves, tinned, drained (2 x 420 g tins)","200 g double cream","250 g mascarpone","40 g vanilla sugar, homemade","100 g flaked almonds"]}],"id":"r104618","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-YBnlkgnXaHg\/XZWfKIVr8LI\/AAAAAAAAe_w\/gAFPpkwu-qEl_wuTefkI1OGYY8iFW31gACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_pkmUWQ1JnHSLO3fx.png","title":"Chocolate Peach Trifle","publishedAt":"2017-06-19T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"9 g","fat":"30 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"39 g","calories":"1919 kJ \/ 459 kcal"},"usefulItems":"spring form tin (Ø 26 cm), baking paper, wire rack, large serving bowl, 8 individual serving bowls or glasses, long sharp knife, non-stick frying pan, oven, refrigerator, hob","hintsAndTricks":["For a grown up version, sprinkle sponge with peach juice and your favourite liqueur.<br>"],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","1h 20m","8 portions"]}